    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In architecture, engineering, and other fields, the discipline that does structural analysis to study and predict the behavior of structures as subjected to dynamic actions, such as acceleration and loading. Dynamic loads include people, wind, waves, traffic, earthquakes, and blasts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
